	<body>
		<category name="Allegiance Class Mods">
			<category name="Description">
				<comment>By Aaron0000</comment>
				<comment>Modifies most of the Tiny Tina Class Mods and turns them into Allegiance COMs for all manufacturers.</comment>
				<comment>Class Mods have their own name instead of just "xxxxx Allegiance", along with skin changes.</comment>
				<comment>All Allegiance COMs can now spawn as a Legendary variant.</comment>
				<comment>Chaotic Evil Class Mods remain unaltered by this mod. This means that Chaotic Evil COMs can spawn as Legendary too despite not actually getting extra benefit out of it. Recommend using the Chaotic Evil COMs from Class Mods Redux if yoou want to address that.</comment>
				<comment>Designed with vanilla Allegiance relics in mind (though not necessary).</comment>
				<comment>(Credit to SirUmnei for the UI fix as well as a source of inspiration, and Mike for a bit of UI fixing).</comment>
				<comment>NOTES;</comment>
				<comment>If using my Class Mods Redux pack, load them before this mod so this mod can overwrite the changes made by Class Mods Redux.</comment>
				<comment>The full name of the coms won't show up in the UI underneath the experience bar and other player's huds, due to how the prefixes and titles were re-rigged.</comment>
				<comment>Each class mod is reskinned. If you want to turn off the skins, uncheck the "Skin" folders.</comment>
				<comment>There's an option at the bottom to fix some of the Class Mods for BLassic, mostly dealing with fixing Hyperion to no longer boost Hyperion's inverted accuracy scheme that it normally has as well as Dahl burst-fire boosts (when most Dahl weapons in BLassic don't burst anymore.)</comment>
				<comment>Any Class Mod that has Inconcievable, Close Enough, or Nth Degree cannot be boosted past ++4 (or +3 for Nth). This is to prevent literally infinite ammo and such.</comment>
